{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have given the slide show that I gave here two years ago about 2,000 times."},{"time":7000,"text":"I'm giving a short slide show this morning"},{"time":12000,"text":"that I'm giving for the very first time, so --"},{"time":15000,"text":"well it's -- I don't want or need to raise the bar,"},{"time":20000,"text":"I'm actually trying to lower the bar."},{"time":21000,"text":"Because I've cobbled this together"},{"time":26000,"text":"to try to meet the challenge of this session."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31000,"text":"And I was reminded by Karen Armstrong's fantastic presentation"},{"time":36000,"text":"that religion really properly understood"},{"time":42000,"text":"is not about belief, but about behavior."},{"time":45000,"text":"Perhaps we should say the same thing about optimism."},{"time":49000,"text":"How dare we be optimistic?"},{"time":53000,"text":"Optimism is sometimes characterized as a belief, an intellectual posture."},{"time":61000,"text":"As Mahatma Gandhi famously said,"},{"time":64000,"text":"\"You must become the change you wish to see in the world.\""},{"time":67000,"text":"And the outcome about which"},{"time":69000,"text":"we wish to be optimistic is not going to be created"},{"time":74000,"text":"by the belief alone, except to the extent that the belief"},{"time":79000,"text":"brings about new behavior. But the word \"behavior\""},{"time":85000,"text":"is also, I think, sometimes misunderstood in this context."},{"time":89000,"text":"I'm a big advocate of changing"},{"time":92000,"text":"the lightbulbs and buying hybrids,"},{"time":95000,"text":"and Tipper and I put 33 solar panels on our house,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and dug the geothermal wells, and did all of that other stuff."},{"time":104000,"text":"But, as important as it is to change the lightbulbs,"},{"time":108000,"text":"it is more important to change the laws."},{"time":110000,"text":"And when we change our behavior in our daily lives,"},{"time":116000,"text":"we sometimes leave out the citizenship part"},{"time":119000,"text":"and the democracy part. In order to be optimistic about this,"},{"time":126000,"text":"we have to become incredibly active as citizens in our democracy."},{"time":132000,"text":"In order to solve the climate crisis,"},{"time":134000,"text":"we have to solve the democracy crisis."},{"time":137000,"text":"And we have one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"I have been trying to tell this story for a long time."},{"time":144000,"text":"I was reminded of that recently, by a woman"},{"time":148000,"text":"who walked past the table I was sitting at,"},{"time":151000,"text":"just staring at me as she walked past. She was in her 70s,"},{"time":155000,"text":"looked like she had a kind face. I thought nothing of it"},{"time":159000,"text":"until I saw from the corner of my eye"},{"time":162000,"text":"she was walking from the opposite direction,"},{"time":164000,"text":"also just staring at me. And so I said, \"How do you do?\""},{"time":168000,"text":"And she said, \"You know, if you dyed your hair black,"},{"time":171000,"text":"you would look just like Al Gore.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"Many years ago, when I was a young congressman,"},{"time":183000,"text":"I spent an awful lot of time dealing with the challenge"},{"time":187000,"text":"of nuclear arms control -- the nuclear arms race."},{"time":190000,"text":"And the military historians taught me,"},{"time":193000,"text":"during that quest, that military conflicts are typically"},{"time":198000,"text":"put into three categories: local battles,"},{"time":203000,"text":"regional or theater wars, and the rare but all-important"},{"time":208000,"text":"global, world war -- strategic conflicts."},{"time":213000,"text":"And each level of conflict requires a different allocation of resources,"},{"time":218000,"text":"a different approach,"},{"time":220000,"text":"a different organizational model."},{"time":224000,"text":"Environmental challenges fall into the same three categories,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and most of what we think about"},{"time":229000,"text":"are local environmental problems: air pollution, water pollution,"},{"time":232000,"text":"hazardous waste dumps. But there are also"},{"time":236000,"text":"regional environmental problems, like acid rain"},{"time":239000,"text":"from the Midwest to the Northeast, and from Western Europe"},{"time":243000,"text":"to the Arctic, and from the Midwest"},{"time":247000,"text":"out the Mississippi into the dead zone of the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":250000,"text":"And there are lots of those. But the climate crisis"},{"time":252000,"text":"is the rare but all-important"},{"time":254000,"text":"global, or strategic, conflict."},{"time":257000,"text":"Everything is affected. And we have to organize our response"},{"time":262000,"text":"appropriately. We need a worldwide, global mobilization"},{"time":268000,"text":"for renewable energy, conservation, efficiency"},{"time":271000,"text":"and a global transition to a low-carbon economy."},{"time":274000,"text":"We have work to do. And we can mobilize resources"},{"time":278000,"text":"and political will. But the political will"},{"time":282000,"text":"has to be mobilized, in order to mobilize the resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"Let me show you these slides here."},{"time":290000,"text":"I thought I would start with the logo. What's missing here,"},{"time":297000,"text":"of course, is the North Polar ice cap."},{"time":299000,"text":"Greenland remains. Twenty-eight years ago, this is what the"},{"time":306000,"text":"polar ice cap -- the North Polar ice cap -- looked like"},{"time":310000,"text":"at the end of the summer, at the fall equinox."},{"time":314000,"text":"This last fall, I went to the Snow and Ice Data Center"},{"time":318000,"text":"in Boulder, Colorado, and talked to the researchers"},{"time":321000,"text":"here in Monterey at the Naval Postgraduate Laboratory."},{"time":325000,"text":"This is what's happened in the last 28 years."},{"time":329000,"text":"To put it in perspective, 2005 was the previous record."},{"time":334000,"text":"Here's what happened last fall"},{"time":337000,"text":"that has really unnerved the researchers."},{"time":340000,"text":"The North Polar ice cap is the same size geographically --"},{"time":352000,"text":"doesn't look quite the same size --"},{"time":353000,"text":"but it is exactly the same size as the United States,"},{"time":357000,"text":"minus an area roughly equal to the state of Arizona."},{"time":360000,"text":"The amount that disappeared in 2005"},{"time":363000,"text":"was equivalent to everything east of the Mississippi."},{"time":367000,"text":"The extra amount that disappeared last fall"},{"time":371000,"text":"was equivalent to this much. It comes back in the winter,"},{"time":374000,"text":"but not as permanent ice, as thin ice --"},{"time":378000,"text":"vulnerable. The amount remaining could be completely gone"},{"time":384000,"text":"in summer in as little as five years."},{"time":385000,"text":"That puts a lot of pressure on Greenland."},{"time":391000,"text":"Already, around the Arctic Circle --"},{"time":399000,"text":"this is a famous village in Alaska. This is a town"},{"time":403000,"text":"in Newfoundland. Antarctica. Latest studies from NASA."},{"time":412000,"text":"The amount of a moderate-to-severe snow melting"},{"time":415000,"text":"of an area equivalent to the size of California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"\"They were the best of times,"},{"time":422000,"text":"they were the worst of times\": the most famous opening sentence"},{"time":425000,"text":"in English literature. I want to share briefly"},{"time":428000,"text":"a tale of two planets. Earth and Venus"},{"time":431000,"text":"are exactly the same size. Earth's diameter"},{"time":434000,"text":"is about 400 kilometers larger, but essentially the same size."},{"time":439000,"text":"They have exactly the same amount of carbon."},{"time":441000,"text":"But the difference is, on Earth, most of the carbon"},{"time":446000,"text":"has been leeched over time out of the atmosphere,"},{"time":449000,"text":"deposited in the ground as coal, oil,"},{"time":453000,"text":"natural gas, etc. On Venus, most of it"},{"time":456000,"text":"is in the atmosphere. The difference is that our temperature"},{"time":461000,"text":"is 59 degrees on average. On Venus,"},{"time":464000,"text":"it's 855. This is relevant to our current strategy"},{"time":468000,"text":"of taking as much carbon out of the ground as quickly as possible,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and putting it into the atmosphere."},{"time":474000,"text":"It's not because Venus is slightly closer to the Sun."},{"time":477000,"text":"It's three times hotter than Mercury,"},{"time":479000,"text":"which is right next to the Sun. Now, briefly,"},{"time":482000,"text":"here's an image you've seen, as one of the only old images,"},{"time":484000,"text":"but I show it because I want to briefly give you CSI: Climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"The global scientific community says:"},{"time":494000,"text":"man-made global warming pollution, put into the atmosphere,"},{"time":498000,"text":"thickening this, is trapping more of the outgoing infrared."},{"time":500000,"text":"You all know that. At the last"},{"time":501000,"text":"IPCC summary, the scientists wanted to say,"},{"time":505000,"text":"\"How certain are you?\" They wanted to answer that \"99 percent.\""},{"time":508000,"text":"The Chinese objected, and so the compromise was"},{"time":510000,"text":"\"more than 90 percent.\""},{"time":512000,"text":"Now, the skeptics say, \"Oh, wait a minute,"},{"time":515000,"text":"this could be variations in this energy"},{"time":519000,"text":"coming in from the sun.\" If that were true,"},{"time":522000,"text":"the stratosphere would be heated as well as the"},{"time":526000,"text":"lower atmosphere, if it's more coming in."},{"time":529000,"text":"If it's more being trapped on the way out, then you would"},{"time":532000,"text":"expect it to be warmer here and cooler here. Here is the lower atmosphere."},{"time":538000,"text":"Here's the stratosphere: cooler."},{"time":541000,"text":"CSI: Climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"Now, here's the good news. Sixty-eight percent of Americans now believe"},{"time":549000,"text":"that human activity is responsible"},{"time":552000,"text":"for global warming. Sixty-nine percent believe that the Earth is heating up"},{"time":557000,"text":"in a significant way. There has been progress,"},{"time":560000,"text":"but here is the key: when given a list"},{"time":567000,"text":"of challenges to confront, global warming is still listed at near the bottom."},{"time":576000,"text":"What is missing is a sense of urgency."},{"time":579000,"text":"If you agree with the factual analysis,"},{"time":584000,"text":"but you don't feel the sense of urgency,"},{"time":587000,"text":"where does that leave you?"},{"time":588000,"text":"Well, the Alliance for Climate Protection, which I head"},{"time":591000,"text":"in conjunction with Current TV -- who did this pro bono --"},{"time":595000,"text":"did a worldwide contest to do commercials on how to communicate this."},{"time":599000,"text":"This is the winner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648000,"text":"NBC -- I'll show all of the networks here -- the top journalists"},{"time":655000,"text":"for NBC asked 956 questions in 2007"},{"time":659000,"text":"of the presidential candidates: two of them were about"},{"time":662000,"text":"the climate crisis. ABC: 844 questions, two about the climate crisis."},{"time":669000,"text":"Fox: two. CNN: two. CBS: zero."},{"time":679000,"text":"From laughs to tears -- this is one of the older"},{"time":683000,"text":"tobacco commercials."},{"time":685000,"text":"So here's what we're doing."},{"time":687000,"text":"This is gasoline consumption in all of these countries. And us."},{"time":697000,"text":"But it's not just the developed nations."},{"time":703000,"text":"The developing countries are now following us"},{"time":707000,"text":"and accelerating their pace. And actually,"},{"time":709000,"text":"their cumulative emissions this year are the equivalent"},{"time":712000,"text":"to where we were in 1965. And they're catching up"},{"time":715000,"text":"very dramatically. The total concentrations:"},{"time":719000,"text":"by 2025, they will be essentially where we were in 1985."},{"time":725000,"text":"If the wealthy countries were completely missing"},{"time":730000,"text":"from the picture, we would still have this crisis."},{"time":733000,"text":"But we have given to the developing countries"},{"time":737000,"text":"the technologies and the ways of thinking"},{"time":739000,"text":"that are creating the crisis. This is in Bolivia --"},{"time":745000,"text":"over thirty years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"This is peak fishing in a few seconds. The '60s."},{"time":771000,"text":"'70s. '80s. '90s. We have to stop this. And the good news is that we can."},{"time":780000,"text":"We have the technologies."},{"time":784000,"text":"We have to have a unified view of how to go about this:"},{"time":789000,"text":"the struggle against poverty in the world"},{"time":793000,"text":"and the challenge of cutting wealthy country emissions,"},{"time":797000,"text":"all has a single, very simple solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"People say, \"What's the solution?\" Here it is."},{"time":805000,"text":"Put a price on carbon. We need a CO2 tax, revenue neutral,"},{"time":811000,"text":"to replace taxation on employment, which was invented by Bismarck --"},{"time":819000,"text":"and some things have changed"},{"time":820000,"text":"since the 19th century."},{"time":821000,"text":"In the poor world, we have to integrate the responses"},{"time":828000,"text":"to poverty with the solutions to the climate crisis."},{"time":832000,"text":"Plans to fight poverty in Uganda"},{"time":835000,"text":"are mooted, if we do not solve the climate crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"But responses can actually make a huge difference"},{"time":847000,"text":"in the poor countries. This is a proposal"},{"time":852000,"text":"that has been talked about a lot in Europe."},{"time":856000,"text":"This was from Nature magazine. These are concentrating"},{"time":860000,"text":"solar, renewable energy plants, linked in a so-called \"supergrid\""},{"time":867000,"text":"to supply all of the electrical power"},{"time":870000,"text":"to Europe, largely from developing countries -- high-voltage DC currents."},{"time":878000,"text":"This is not pie in the sky; this can be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881000,"text":"We need to do it for our own economy."},{"time":884000,"text":"The latest figures show that the old model"},{"time":887000,"text":"is not working. There are a lot of great investments"},{"time":891000,"text":"that you can make. If you are investing in tar sands"},{"time":895000,"text":"or shale oil, then you have a portfolio"},{"time":901000,"text":"that is crammed with sub-prime carbon assets."},{"time":905000,"text":"And it is based on an old model."},{"time":909000,"text":"Junkies find veins in their toes when the ones"},{"time":912000,"text":"in their arms and their legs collapse. Developing tar sands"},{"time":917000,"text":"and coal shale is the equivalent. Here are just a few of the investments"},{"time":923000,"text":"that I personally think make sense."},{"time":926000,"text":"I have a stake in these, so I'll have a disclaimer there."},{"time":929000,"text":"But geothermal, concentrating solar,"},{"time":932000,"text":"advanced photovoltaics, efficiency and conservation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939000,"text":"You've seen this slide before, but there's a change."},{"time":942000,"text":"The only two countries that didn't ratify"},{"time":946000,"text":"-- and now there's only one. Australia had an election."},{"time":951000,"text":"And there was a campaign in Australia"},{"time":954000,"text":"that involved television and Internet and radio commercials"},{"time":959000,"text":"to lift the sense of urgency for the people there."},{"time":961000,"text":"And we trained 250 people to give the slide show"},{"time":965000,"text":"in every town and village and city in Australia."},{"time":970000,"text":"Lot of other things contributed to it,"},{"time":972000,"text":"but the new Prime Minister announced that"},{"time":975000,"text":"his very first priority would be to change Australia's position"},{"time":979000,"text":"on Kyoto, and he has. Now, they came to an awareness"},{"time":984000,"text":"partly because of the horrible drought that they have had."},{"time":988000,"text":"This is Lake Lanier. My friend Heidi Cullen"},{"time":992000,"text":"said that if we gave droughts names the way we give hurricanes names,"},{"time":996000,"text":"we'd call the one in the southeast now Katrina,"},{"time":999000,"text":"and we would say it's headed toward Atlanta."},{"time":1001000,"text":"We can't wait for the kind of drought"},{"time":1005000,"text":"Australia had to change our political culture."},{"time":1007000,"text":"Here's more good news. The cities supporting Kyoto in the U.S."},{"time":1016000,"text":"are up to 780 -- and I thought I saw one go by there,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"just to localize this -- which is good news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025000,"text":"Now, to close, we heard a couple of days ago"},{"time":1031000,"text":"about the value of making individual heroism so commonplace"},{"time":1040000,"text":"that it becomes banal or routine."},{"time":1043000,"text":"What we need is another hero generation. Those of us who are alive"},{"time":1052000,"text":"in the United States of America"},{"time":1054000,"text":"today especially, but also the rest of the world,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"have to somehow understand that history"},{"time":1062000,"text":"has presented us with a choice -- just as Jill [Bolte] Taylor was figuring out"},{"time":1072000,"text":"how to save her life while she was distracted"},{"time":1077000,"text":"by the amazing experience that she was going through."},{"time":1081000,"text":"We now have a culture of distraction."},{"time":1084000,"text":"But we have a planetary emergency."},{"time":1089000,"text":"And we have to find a way to create,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"in the generation of those alive today, a sense of generational mission."},{"time":1099000,"text":"I wish I could find the words to convey this."},{"time":1105000,"text":"This was another hero generation"},{"time":1107000,"text":"that brought democracy to the planet."},{"time":1110000,"text":"Another that ended slavery. And that gave women the right to vote."},{"time":1117000,"text":"We can do this. Don't tell me that we don't have the capacity to do it."},{"time":1124000,"text":"If we had just one week's worth of what we spend on the Iraq War,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"we could be well on the way to solving this challenge."},{"time":1131000,"text":"We have the capacity to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1141000,"text":"One final point: I'm optimistic, because I believe"},{"time":1154000,"text":"we have the capacity, at moments of great challenge,"},{"time":1158000,"text":"to set aside the causes of distraction and rise to the challenge"},{"time":1164000,"text":"that history is presenting to us."},{"time":1169000,"text":"Sometimes I hear people respond to the disturbing facts of the climate crisis"},{"time":1181000,"text":"by saying, \"Oh, this is so terrible."},{"time":1183000,"text":"What a burden we have.\" I would like to ask you"},{"time":1189000,"text":"to reframe that. How many generations"},{"time":1193000,"text":"in all of human history have had the opportunity"},{"time":1198000,"text":"to rise to a challenge that is worthy of our best efforts?"},{"time":1207000,"text":"A challenge that can pull from us"},{"time":1213000,"text":"more than we knew we could do? I think we ought to approach"},{"time":1221000,"text":"this challenge with a sense of profound joy"},{"time":1225000,"text":"and gratitude that we are the generation"},{"time":1230000,"text":"about which, a thousand years from now,"},{"time":1234000,"text":"philharmonic orchestras and poets and singers will celebrate"},{"time":1243000,"text":"by saying, they were the ones that found it within themselves"},{"time":1250000,"text":"to solve this crisis and lay the basis"},{"time":1255000,"text":"for a bright and optimistic human future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1257000,"text":"Let's do that. Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1284000,"text":"Chris Anderson: For so many people at TED, there is deep pain"},{"time":1290000,"text":"that basically a design issue"},{"time":1292000,"text":"on a voting form --"},{"time":1294000,"text":"one bad design issue meant that your voice wasn't being heard"},{"time":1298000,"text":"like that in the last eight years in a position"},{"time":1299000,"text":"where you could make these things come true."},{"time":1301000,"text":"That hurts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1303000,"text":"Al Gore: You have no idea. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313000,"text":"CA: When you look at what the leading candidates"},{"time":1314000,"text":"in your own party are doing now -- I mean, there's --"},{"time":1316000,"text":"are you excited by their plans on global warming?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1330000,"text":"AG: The answer to the question is hard for me"},{"time":1334000,"text":"because, on the one hand, I think that"},{"time":1338000,"text":"we should feel really great about the fact"},{"time":1343000,"text":"that the Republican nominee -- certain nominee --"},{"time":1349000,"text":"John McCain, and both of the finalists"},{"time":1353000,"text":"for the Democratic nomination -- all three have a very different"},{"time":1358000,"text":"and forward-leaning position"},{"time":1360000,"text":"on the climate crisis. All three have offered leadership,"},{"time":1365000,"text":"and all three are very different from the approach taken"},{"time":1369000,"text":"by the current administration. And I think"},{"time":1372000,"text":"that all three have also been responsible in"},{"time":1376000,"text":"putting forward plans and proposals. But the campaign dialogue that --"},{"time":1387000,"text":"as illustrated by the questions --"},{"time":1388000,"text":"that was put together by the"},{"time":1389000,"text":"League of Conservation Voters, by the way, the analysis of all the questions --"},{"time":1392000,"text":"and, by the way, the debates have all been"},{"time":1396000,"text":"sponsored by something that goes by the Orwellian label,"},{"time":1398000,"text":"\"Clean Coal.\" Has anybody noticed that?"},{"time":1402000,"text":"Every single debate has been sponsored by \"Clean Coal.\""},{"time":1406000,"text":"\"Now, even lower emissions!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1408000,"text":"The richness and fullness of the dialogue"},{"time":1412000,"text":"in our democracy has not laid the basis"},{"time":1415000,"text":"for the kind of bold initiative that is really needed."},{"time":1419000,"text":"So they're saying the right things and they may --"},{"time":1422000,"text":"whichever of them is elected -- may do the right thing,"},{"time":1425000,"text":"but let me tell you: when I came back from Kyoto"},{"time":1429000,"text":"in 1997, with a feeling of great happiness"},{"time":1436000,"text":"that we'd gotten that breakthrough there,"},{"time":1438000,"text":"and then confronted the United States Senate,"},{"time":1440000,"text":"only one out of 100 senators was willing to vote"},{"time":1444000,"text":"to confirm, to ratify that treaty. Whatever the candidates say"},{"time":1451000,"text":"has to be laid alongside what the people say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1456000,"text":"This challenge is part of the fabric"},{"time":1460000,"text":"of our whole civilization."},{"time":1462000,"text":"CO2 is the exhaling breath of our civilization, literally."},{"time":1466000,"text":"And now we mechanized that process. Changing that pattern"},{"time":1469000,"text":"requires a scope, a scale, a speed of change"},{"time":1476000,"text":"that is beyond what we have done in the past."},{"time":1479000,"text":"So that's why I began by saying,"},{"time":1481000,"text":"be optimistic in what you do, but be an active citizen."},{"time":1488000,"text":"Demand -- change the light bulbs,"},{"time":1490000,"text":"but change the laws. Change the global treaties."},{"time":1493000,"text":"We have to speak up. We have to solve this democracy -- this --"},{"time":1500000,"text":"We have sclerosis in our democracy. And we have to change that."},{"time":1507000,"text":"Use the Internet. Go on the Internet."},{"time":1508000,"text":"Connect with people. Become very active as citizens."},{"time":1512000,"text":"Have a moratorium -- we shouldn't"},{"time":1514000,"text":"have any new coal-fired generating plants"},{"time":1516000,"text":"that aren't able to capture and store CO2, which means we have to"},{"time":1521000,"text":"quickly build these renewable sources."},{"time":1523000,"text":"Now, nobody is talking on that scale. But I do believe"},{"time":1527000,"text":"that between now and November, it is possible."},{"time":1531000,"text":"This Alliance for Climate Protection"},{"time":1533000,"text":"is going to launch a nationwide campaign --"},{"time":1536000,"text":"grassroots mobilization, television ads, Internet ads,"},{"time":1539000,"text":"radio, newspaper -- with partnerships with everybody"},{"time":1542000,"text":"from the Girl Scouts to the hunters and fishermen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1545000,"text":"We need help. We need help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1549000,"text":"CA: In terms of your own personal role going forward,"},{"time":1553000,"text":"Al, is there something more than that"},{"time":1555000,"text":"you would like to be doing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1556000,"text":"AG: I have prayed that I would be able to find the answer"},{"time":1564000,"text":"to that question. What can I do?"},{"time":1569000,"text":"Buckminster Fuller once wrote, \"If the future"},{"time":1573000,"text":"of all human civilization depended on me, what would I do?"},{"time":1578000,"text":"How would I be?\" It does depend on all of us,"},{"time":1583000,"text":"but again, not just with the light bulbs."},{"time":1585000,"text":"We, most of us here, are Americans. We have a democracy."},{"time":1593000,"text":"We can change things, but we have to actively change."},{"time":1599000,"text":"What's needed really is a higher level of consciousness."},{"time":1604000,"text":"And that's hard to --"},{"time":1606000,"text":"that's hard to create -- but it is coming."},{"time":1610000,"text":"There's an old African proverb that some of you know"},{"time":1613000,"text":"that says, \"If you want to go quickly, go alone;"},{"time":1617000,"text":"if you want to go far, go together.\" We have to go far, quickly."},{"time":1625000,"text":"So we have to have a change in consciousness."},{"time":1629000,"text":"A change in commitment. A new sense of urgency."},{"time":1633000,"text":"A new appreciation for the privilege"},{"time":1636000,"text":"that we have of undertaking this challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1639000,"text":"CA: Al Gore, thank you so much for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1643000,"text":"AG: Thank you. Thank you very much."}]}]}